WEBVTT

00:06.758 --> 00:08.034
[horse neighing]

00:08.103 --> 00:11.655
- [shushes]
Easy.

00:11.724 --> 00:14.586
Easy now.

00:14.655 --> 00:17.000
That's right.

00:17.068 --> 00:20.103
Just like that.

00:20.172 --> 00:22.448
Take this real slow.

00:22.517 --> 00:27.241
[horse neighs]

00:27.310 --> 00:30.689
[grunts]
God...

00:30.758 --> 00:33.448
- That is some gift.

00:33.517 --> 00:37.034
- God damn that boy.

00:39.793 --> 00:42.586
Easy, easy.
There you go.

00:42.655 --> 00:46.931
[horse neighing]

00:47.000 --> 00:49.758
[fence thumps and rattles]

00:55.068 --> 00:58.000
[horse neighs]

01:05.241 --> 01:07.655
I think
I got him settled now.

01:07.724 --> 01:08.965
[grunts]

01:09.034 --> 01:11.103
[horse neighs]

01:11.172 --> 01:12.620
- Whoa, he's going over.

01:12.689 --> 01:14.965
[horse squeals]

01:15.034 --> 01:18.310
- God.

01:18.379 --> 01:21.034
- That's one rank son
of a bitch right there.

01:21.103 --> 01:22.517
You ought to take him
chest high in the river

01:22.586 --> 01:23.965
and see how much buck
he's got then.

01:24.034 --> 01:26.310
- No, no, this one, uh...

01:26.379 --> 01:29.413
This one may surprise you.
Look at this, now he's my...

01:29.482 --> 01:31.586
Now he's my best
goddamned friend.

01:31.655 --> 01:33.172
- Well, you want me
to give him a go?

01:33.241 --> 01:35.103
- No, hell no.

01:35.172 --> 01:40.068
This is a job for a young man
with rubber bones.

01:40.137 --> 01:44.275
- You know, that horse will
make a hand out of someone.

01:49.482 --> 01:53.068
That's a good idea.
I'll be right back.

01:53.137 --> 01:56.206
Hey, Jimmy, go ahead
and put that down.

01:56.275 --> 01:58.206
[duct tape screeching]

01:58.275 --> 02:00.172
- Look, I don't know
nothing about horses.

02:00.241 --> 02:01.827
- Well, you're getting
a crash course, Jimmy.

02:01.896 --> 02:03.965
[horse snorts]
- Should I pet him?

02:04.034 --> 02:06.241
- [laughs] I don't think it's
gonna make much difference.

02:06.310 --> 02:07.448
- You got it on your side?

02:07.517 --> 02:09.103
- Yeah, I'm good.

02:09.172 --> 02:10.586
You pull this,
so you don't flip back,

02:10.655 --> 02:13.275
you understand?
All right?

02:13.344 --> 02:15.896
He's gonna hate it for shit,
but whatever you do, Jimmy,

02:15.965 --> 02:17.620
don't you let go.

02:17.689 --> 02:19.310
- Look, can we just--can we
talk about this for a second?

02:19.379 --> 02:21.034
- Good luck, Jimmy.
- 20 on the horse.

02:21.103 --> 02:22.586
- I got 40 on the ball.

02:22.655 --> 02:24.482
- I'd expect some resistance.

02:24.551 --> 02:25.482
- Define resistance.

02:25.551 --> 02:27.310
- You be quiet.

02:27.379 --> 02:31.241
Resistance the kind of thing
that defines itself, Jimmy.

02:32.758 --> 02:34.103
Let's go.

02:34.172 --> 02:35.103
- Kick him.

02:35.172 --> 02:39.103
[horse neighs]

02:39.172 --> 02:40.758
- Pull in those reins, Jimmy.

02:40.827 --> 02:42.551
[overlapping chatter]

02:42.620 --> 02:44.965
[horse neighing]

02:45.034 --> 02:46.931
- Whoo!

02:47.000 --> 02:48.965
- Pull your reins in, Jimmy.

02:49.034 --> 02:51.379
- Whoo-hoo!

02:51.448 --> 02:54.068
- God damn, that thing's
a freight train.

02:54.137 --> 02:55.827
[horse snorts]

02:55.896 --> 02:58.586
- Whoo-whee, I don't miss
being low man.

02:58.655 --> 03:02.206
[horse neighing]

03:02.275 --> 03:05.482
- Low man's what turns you
into cowboys.

03:05.551 --> 03:08.620
It'll make him one too.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.827
- [laughs]

03:10.896 --> 03:13.620
[orchestral western music]

03:13.689 --> 03:20.724
♪ ♪

04:12.965 --> 04:16.482
[engine revving]

04:22.344 --> 04:26.413
- [screams]

04:26.482 --> 04:30.482
Fuck, God damn it.
Piece of shit.

04:32.172 --> 04:35.379
Son of a bitch.
Piece of fucking shit.

04:35.448 --> 04:38.827
God--
[grunts]

04:43.827 --> 04:45.931
- What happened
to the tractor?

04:46.000 --> 04:47.551
- I flipped it.

04:47.620 --> 04:50.413
- Why'd you do that?

04:50.482 --> 04:53.379
What's that for?

04:53.448 --> 04:55.379
- Get in the house.

04:55.448 --> 04:58.689
[metal clanks]

05:04.896 --> 05:06.862
- I think the tractor's
already dead.

05:06.931 --> 05:10.931
- Get in the goddamned house.
- [sighs]

05:15.000 --> 05:17.000
- Porch ain't inside.

05:17.068 --> 05:19.000
- I don't care!

05:19.068 --> 05:21.965
- Suit yourself.

05:22.034 --> 05:26.482
Hey, I want you to do
exactly as I say, okay?

05:26.551 --> 05:28.310
Cover your ears.

05:28.379 --> 05:31.275
Open your mouth real wide,
like you're at the dentist.

05:31.344 --> 05:35.655
Stay just like that,
you hear me?

05:42.482 --> 05:44.896
- Aah!

05:46.862 --> 05:49.896
- You can close your mouth now.

05:51.517 --> 05:54.068
- Why didn't you do that
in the first place?

05:56.103 --> 05:58.310
- Was that you?

05:58.379 --> 05:59.793
Are you out of
your fucking mind?

05:59.862 --> 06:01.413
- That's why.

06:01.482 --> 06:05.482
Sorry, babe, there was
a thing with the...tractor.

06:10.137 --> 06:11.379
Uh-oh.

06:11.448 --> 06:13.931
- Mama owes me a dollar.

06:14.000 --> 06:17.206
- Yeah, have fun trying
to collect that.

06:17.275 --> 06:20.103
- You're gonna be
in a big time out.

06:20.172 --> 06:24.103
- I'm already
in a time out, son.

06:24.172 --> 06:27.103
[ominous music]

06:27.172 --> 06:33.517
♪ ♪

06:33.586 --> 06:35.551
- [gasps]

06:35.620 --> 06:38.206
You found a dinosaur.

06:38.275 --> 06:40.482
Oh.
[giggles]

06:40.551 --> 06:44.551
♪ ♪

06:44.620 --> 06:47.000
[footsteps pattering]

06:47.068 --> 06:50.103
- Mr. Dutton.
Mr. Dutton.

06:50.172 --> 06:51.965
Mr. Dutton.

06:52.034 --> 06:55.965
The Governor wants to see you.

06:56.034 --> 07:00.103
- Sure thing.

07:01.172 --> 07:02.724
[telephone ringing]

07:02.793 --> 07:05.793
- Governor Perry's office.

07:08.448 --> 07:10.103
- Morning.

07:10.172 --> 07:13.413
There's things we'd like
to talk to you about.

07:13.482 --> 07:15.137
- Things like your future.

07:15.206 --> 07:17.586
- I'd like that.
- So would we.

07:17.655 --> 07:20.448
But first, there's something
else we have to talk about.

07:20.517 --> 07:23.000
- Have a seat.

07:24.896 --> 07:26.310
- What's this?

07:26.379 --> 07:29.068
- Nothing,
because you never saw it.

07:29.137 --> 07:32.931
- Okay.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.068
- The bullet wound inflicted
on your brother

07:35.137 --> 07:37.482
severed his spinal column
at C7,

07:37.551 --> 07:39.448
which would leave him paralyzed
from the chest down,

07:39.517 --> 07:42.931
including his arms
from his elbow to his fingers.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.620
Would've been impossible
for him to fire a pistol,

07:45.689 --> 07:50.413
which means there was
a third shooter.

07:50.482 --> 07:52.103
- Well, what does that matter?
Um...

07:52.172 --> 07:53.517
Self-defense is self-defense,

07:53.586 --> 07:55.172
even if someone else
pulled the trigger.

07:55.241 --> 07:57.241
- Isn't that simple, Jamie.

07:57.310 --> 07:58.827
- No matter who
pulled the trigger,

07:58.896 --> 08:03.206
it wasn't self-defense.
It was an execution.

08:03.275 --> 08:06.034
The medical examiner hasn't
released his findings yet.

08:06.103 --> 08:10.586
But when he does, it'll go
to BIA, FBI, state police,

08:10.655 --> 08:13.241
each of whom will want their
own forensic pathologist

08:13.310 --> 08:14.931
to have a look at the body.

08:15.000 --> 08:17.344
- Then it starts
screaming "cover up."

08:17.413 --> 08:19.896
And it's screaming it
at your father.

08:19.965 --> 08:22.655
- The real concern is
who it screams at next.

08:22.724 --> 08:25.586
Two BLM agents stated seeing
another rider on the horse

08:25.655 --> 08:27.689
with Lee when he arrived
at the Yellowstone.

08:27.758 --> 08:30.965
- What did they, um...
Did they identify him?

08:31.034 --> 08:32.861
- They're friends.

08:32.931 --> 08:34.861
Friends forget things.

08:34.931 --> 08:38.758
But some of this starts
adding up real quick, Jamie.

08:38.827 --> 08:40.688
This is already national news.

08:40.758 --> 08:42.379
Add a racially-motivated
killing

08:42.448 --> 08:44.344
by an officer of
your father's agency--

08:44.413 --> 08:46.620
- I'll have to start
chopping heads,

08:46.689 --> 08:47.793
or it's mine on the block.

08:47.862 --> 08:49.448
- What're you saying?

08:49.517 --> 08:52.620
- He's saying,
"Don't up us in that position."

08:52.689 --> 08:55.551
- Okay, um, I just--

08:55.620 --> 08:56.931
I could use some time here.

08:57.000 --> 08:58.310
Ho--how long can you
hold this report?

08:58.379 --> 09:00.758
- A week, maybe.

09:00.827 --> 09:03.896
- I'll get into it.
[clears throat]

09:03.965 --> 09:05.793
- Do it fast.

09:05.862 --> 09:08.724
This is the kind of ship
that sinks everyone.

09:08.793 --> 09:12.793
- That's the only kind of ship
I ever find myself on.

09:14.827 --> 09:17.758
[foreboding music]

09:17.827 --> 09:22.482
♪ ♪

09:22.551 --> 09:23.827
- [grunts]

09:23.896 --> 09:27.793
- [knocks door]
- Yeah.

09:27.862 --> 09:31.000
- Are you sick?
- Do I look sick?

09:31.068 --> 09:33.310
- You're in bed at noon, a
dozen pill bottles beside you.

09:33.379 --> 09:34.551
Yeah, I'd say you look sick.

09:34.620 --> 09:36.068
- I'm on vacation.

09:36.137 --> 09:37.517
- Oh, is that what
you're calling it now?

09:37.586 --> 09:40.862
- What do you want?

09:42.137 --> 09:44.517
[clears throat]

09:44.586 --> 09:47.827
This feels very serious.

09:47.896 --> 09:51.551
- [sighs]

09:51.620 --> 09:53.206
I could use some advice.

09:53.275 --> 09:54.793
- Yes, I know you're gay.

09:54.862 --> 09:59.241
No, Daddy will not still love
you when you tell him.

09:59.310 --> 10:03.310
- I'm wasting my fucking time
asking you for help.

10:04.827 --> 10:09.034
You know, if being here is so
terrible for you, Beth...

10:11.034 --> 10:13.275
you can go back to Salt Lake.
- You asked for advice.

10:13.344 --> 10:14.896
I gave it.

10:14.965 --> 10:17.758
- Well, you know, I'm not gay.
I'm celibate.

10:17.827 --> 10:19.862
Because I am terrified
to get somebody pregnant,

10:19.931 --> 10:21.931
pass on the gene that made you.

10:22.000 --> 10:26.000
- Good one.

10:39.172 --> 10:42.206
- Well, you're almost a winner.

10:42.275 --> 10:45.275
- Day ain't over yet.

10:46.793 --> 10:51.068
- We have a problem.

10:51.137 --> 10:54.034
- You don't have a solution?

10:54.103 --> 10:55.862
- It requires a few.

10:55.931 --> 10:58.275
And you're not gonna like
any of them.

10:58.344 --> 11:01.275
- Did they identify Kayce?

11:01.344 --> 11:04.344
- Not yet.

11:05.586 --> 11:08.344
- Who are the agents
we're talking about?

11:08.413 --> 11:12.517
- It's, uh, Tom Reynolds
and Aaron McReary.

11:12.586 --> 11:14.724
- Reynolds I can deal with.

11:14.793 --> 11:16.517
I don't know this McReary.

11:16.586 --> 11:18.482
- Yeah, he lives in
the south end of the valley.

11:18.551 --> 11:20.827
Word is he likes his religion.

11:20.896 --> 11:23.413
As in "won't tell a lie"
likes it?

11:23.482 --> 11:25.413
- Yeah, that would be my guess.

11:25.482 --> 11:27.896
- Find out where
he goes to church.

11:27.965 --> 11:30.275
Anything else?

11:30.344 --> 11:33.310
Anything else?
You said there were a few.

11:33.379 --> 11:35.448
- [sighs]

11:35.517 --> 11:38.793
The medical examiner's report.

11:38.862 --> 11:41.896
You're not gonna like it.

11:43.655 --> 11:45.172
- Who else has seen the report?

11:45.241 --> 11:48.655
- The only ones who have
seen it want it to change.

11:48.724 --> 11:51.620
- Then it'll change.
- It means they're doctors.

11:51.689 --> 11:56.172
Which means they took an oath,
and it wasn't to you.

11:56.241 --> 11:58.655
No matter what we do,
the photographs won't change.

11:58.724 --> 12:00.517
The body won't change.
It'll tell the same story

12:00.586 --> 12:01.586
to anybody who looks.
- The body's buried, Jamie.

12:01.655 --> 12:03.103
Relax.

12:03.172 --> 12:04.931
- Yeah, but when they
see the report...

12:05.000 --> 12:06.862
[horse snorts]

12:06.931 --> 12:09.206
- When they see the report,
what?

12:09.275 --> 12:10.758
- When they see--

12:10.827 --> 12:13.896
- You think I'm just gonna
let them dig up my son?

12:13.965 --> 12:16.034
- When they see the report,
they won't ask.

12:16.103 --> 12:19.172
They're just gonna do it, Dad.

12:19.241 --> 12:21.241
I think we should--
- No, don't say that.

12:21.310 --> 12:22.724
- I think we should
beat them to it.

12:22.793 --> 12:26.206
- All right, don't say it.
Don't even think it.

12:26.275 --> 12:28.068
[tense music]

12:28.137 --> 12:29.241
- Kayce shot him
in the forehead

12:29.310 --> 12:30.931
while he laid
on his back.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.310
- We don't know it was Kayce.
- He was executed.

12:33.379 --> 12:37.241
Five bullets in a circle,
like this.

12:37.310 --> 12:40.241
Name a livestock officer
who could do that.

12:40.310 --> 12:45.517
♪ ♪

12:45.586 --> 12:48.482
- I need to hear him
say it first.

12:48.551 --> 12:50.758
♪ ♪

12:55.206 --> 12:56.551
- You know, there was a time

12:56.620 --> 12:59.379
when most of Montana
was under the ocean.

12:59.448 --> 13:00.758
- Really?

13:00.827 --> 13:02.551
- Yeah, and I'm betting that--

13:02.620 --> 13:04.448
I'm betting that right here--

13:04.517 --> 13:06.724
I reckon right here
was the beach.

13:06.793 --> 13:08.482
'Cause you see this?

13:08.551 --> 13:10.413
I'm thinking these washed up
on the shore,

13:10.482 --> 13:12.275
and your buddy here,
the dinosaur,

13:12.344 --> 13:16.068
he's probably out walking,
looking for dinner right here.

13:16.137 --> 13:18.137
- Then what happened?
- I don't know.

13:18.206 --> 13:20.000
Hard to say.

13:20.068 --> 13:21.827
Maybe something...

13:21.896 --> 13:24.413
[chuckling] Something made
a dinner out of him.

13:24.482 --> 13:27.758
- Like what?
- Mm.

13:27.827 --> 13:30.344
Maybe a 'CAUSE. shark.

13:30.413 --> 13:32.241
- How big are those?

13:32.310 --> 13:36.689
- From here
to the round corral.

13:36.758 --> 13:40.620
- That's a big fish.
- That's a big fish.

13:40.689 --> 13:41.931
- I don't wanna
catch that fish.

13:42.000 --> 13:43.344
- No, me neither.

13:43.413 --> 13:45.068
Don't ever wanna see
a fish like that.

13:45.137 --> 13:47.896
- Do you think some day
an explorer will find our bones

13:47.965 --> 13:50.000
and wonder what happened to us?

13:50.068 --> 13:53.655
- I think after us, Tate,

13:53.724 --> 13:55.655
the exploring's all done.

13:55.724 --> 13:59.758
You, uh, keep it up.

14:01.000 --> 14:04.931
I'm gonna talk to
your daddy a bit.

14:09.551 --> 14:11.655
Jesus Christ, what...

14:11.724 --> 14:13.517
What happened here?

14:13.586 --> 14:17.724
- Long story.
- I need to ask you something.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.517
- I already told you.

14:22.586 --> 14:26.724
- I need the truth this time.
- I told you the truth.

14:27.896 --> 14:31.758
- Yes, you're such a boy.
This ain't checkers, son.

14:31.827 --> 14:35.620
This is chess, and you're
about to play it with masters.

14:35.689 --> 14:37.482
Now, these people,
they're gonna twist you

14:37.551 --> 14:39.655
into so many knots, you won't
know where the truth begins

14:39.724 --> 14:41.758
and your future ends.

14:41.827 --> 14:44.068
Now, brothers get their
secrets, all right?

14:44.137 --> 14:47.344
But he was my son.

14:47.413 --> 14:50.965
I deserve to know.

14:51.034 --> 14:53.137
- What happened that night
stays where it is.

14:53.206 --> 14:55.275
- No, sir.

14:55.344 --> 14:57.482
No, sir, not a thing on this
planet stays where it is.

14:57.551 --> 15:02.034
Not one.

15:02.103 --> 15:05.034
At least tell me this.
Did...

15:05.103 --> 15:07.413
[ominous music]

15:07.482 --> 15:11.344
Did he get to see it coming?

15:11.413 --> 15:15.206
- He saw it coming.

15:15.275 --> 15:19.068
♪ ♪

15:19.137 --> 15:22.137
- [sighs]

15:24.413 --> 15:26.172
- What'd he say?

15:26.241 --> 15:28.827
- We need that medical
examiner to take a new oath.

15:28.896 --> 15:32.275
- [sighs]

15:32.344 --> 15:34.172
- What?

15:34.241 --> 15:37.517
- Um, asking the medical
examiner to sit on the report

15:37.586 --> 15:39.068
didn't go over so well.

15:39.137 --> 15:41.344
He shared Long's autopsy
with the tribal police.

15:41.413 --> 15:43.068
- God.

15:43.137 --> 15:47.241
God damn it.

15:47.310 --> 15:50.344
[sighs]
All right.

15:50.413 --> 15:53.379
What do we know about
this son of a bitch?

15:53.448 --> 15:56.034
- He used to be the medical
examiner in Chicago.

15:56.103 --> 15:57.758
He was asked to resign.

15:57.827 --> 16:00.931
Got caught smoking
embalming fluid.

16:01.000 --> 16:02.620
- Smoking what?

16:02.689 --> 16:05.344
- Smoking embalming fluid.

16:05.413 --> 16:07.586
- Jesus Christ.

16:07.655 --> 16:10.965
- Oh, if he was fired,
and the cause came out,

16:11.034 --> 16:14.551
every finding he's ever issued
will be ruled inadmissible.

16:14.620 --> 16:18.620
I think I can push this.
You want me to?

16:23.517 --> 16:27.379
- Let me think about it.

16:27.448 --> 16:29.758
No...

16:29.827 --> 16:31.655
Send Rip.

16:31.724 --> 16:34.310
I won't negotiate
with a drug addict.

16:40.517 --> 16:44.655
- Well, it's an even bet
who quits first.

16:44.724 --> 16:46.275
- Yeah?

16:46.344 --> 16:49.241
That boy quit hours ago.

16:49.310 --> 16:50.620
If he wasn't strapped to the
saddle,

16:50.689 --> 16:52.620
he'd be laying
in the dirt.

16:52.689 --> 16:57.241
- Yeah, he'll be a cowboy
before sundown.

16:57.310 --> 16:59.827
- It's just a favor, Rip.

16:59.896 --> 17:03.137
And I'm afraid that's all
he'll ever be.

17:03.206 --> 17:07.931
- It's a pretty good shot.

17:08.000 --> 17:10.758
- Yeah, that is
a pretty good shot.

17:10.827 --> 17:12.896
- Hard to call
that self-defense.

17:12.964 --> 17:15.689
If Lee Dutton was alive,
I'd press charges.

17:15.758 --> 17:18.172
- Are we sure Lee Dutton
is the one who did it?

17:18.241 --> 17:20.344
- As we can be.

17:20.413 --> 17:22.034
I mean, I'm not sure
what difference it makes

17:22.103 --> 17:24.550
at this point.

17:24.619 --> 17:27.275
- I'll tell you
what difference it makes.

17:27.344 --> 17:30.172
Right now we have a tragedy.

17:30.241 --> 17:32.310
If there is a third shooter,

17:32.379 --> 17:35.275
we have something
entirely different.

17:35.344 --> 17:40.034
We have the int
of John Dutton right here.

17:40.103 --> 17:41.655
And there's no witnesses,
right?

17:41.724 --> 17:45.206
- The only person near
this scene was Kayce.

17:45.275 --> 17:48.931
He may be on our side with
cattle, but this is different.

17:49.000 --> 17:53.379
- Kayce Dutton.
- Yeah, the hero.

17:53.448 --> 17:55.827
- The soldier.

17:55.896 --> 17:58.931
[menacing music]

18:00.275 --> 18:02.931
- Whoa, easy.

18:03.000 --> 18:05.793
- Pull him down.

18:05.862 --> 18:09.206
- Easy.
Easy.

18:11.620 --> 18:14.655
There you go.

18:16.482 --> 18:19.379
Come on.

18:19.448 --> 18:22.482
- [grunts]

18:24.344 --> 18:27.344
[sniffles, spits]

18:29.517 --> 18:32.448
- Over there.

18:32.517 --> 18:35.551
Nice and easy.

18:40.689 --> 18:44.586
[smacks lips]
Come on, come on.

18:44.655 --> 18:47.586
[stirring music]

18:47.655 --> 18:48.724
♪ ♪

18:48.793 --> 18:52.137
Whoa, whoa, be easy.

18:52.206 --> 18:57.586
♪ ♪

18:57.655 --> 19:00.655
Easy.

19:00.724 --> 19:03.931
♪ ♪

19:04.000 --> 19:07.172
Jimmy.

19:07.241 --> 19:11.517
You go bathe him, tie him up,
and no hay until he cools off.

19:11.586 --> 19:14.517
Go on.

19:14.586 --> 19:21.620
♪ ♪

19:24.034 --> 19:27.965
Well, the son of a bitch
is broken now.

19:28.034 --> 19:31.586
♪ ♪

19:31.655 --> 19:35.172
- Oh.
[retches]

19:35.241 --> 19:37.896
- Here we go.
- Yeah.

19:37.965 --> 19:41.965
There may be a little cowboy
in him after all.

19:45.413 --> 19:47.827
- I don't have the energy
for you today.

19:47.896 --> 19:51.896
- Never thought of energy
as something you lacked.

19:54.724 --> 19:58.482
Take me anywhere
but a music festival.

19:58.551 --> 20:00.103
- Beth, I thought you
liked music.

20:00.172 --> 20:01.793
That's why I suggested it.

20:01.862 --> 20:03.482
- Still like music.

20:03.551 --> 20:07.551
The festival part
that bothers me.

20:16.172 --> 20:20.172
Pick something more suited
to my personality.

20:21.586 --> 20:23.275
- You wanna go get drunk,

20:23.344 --> 20:26.413
and watch some wolves
kill an elk in a park?

20:29.034 --> 20:32.344
- I'll drive.

20:32.413 --> 20:34.793
- Ladies and gentlemen,
thanks for coming out...

20:34.862 --> 20:36.655
[cheers and applause]

20:36.724 --> 20:39.551
We got some top cowboys
in the bull riding event.

20:39.620 --> 20:42.000
And our first cowboy out
will be Toby Reynolds.

20:42.068 --> 20:45.517
- Come on now, Toby, let's go.

20:45.586 --> 20:48.275
- All right, Toby's got
a cheering section.

20:48.344 --> 20:50.000
Here we go!
Toby Reynolds.

20:50.068 --> 20:51.448
[bull groans]

20:51.517 --> 20:53.068
[rock music]

20:53.137 --> 20:55.965
♪ ♪

20:56.034 --> 21:00.172
Toby's staying in the middle.
Time's up.

21:00.241 --> 21:02.586
Almost a qualified rider.

21:02.655 --> 21:05.827
- Shaves a year off my life
every time I see him ride.

21:05.896 --> 21:09.068
- Shaves a year off mine.
He's your kid.

21:09.137 --> 21:12.275
- How you kept your boys out
of rodeo I'll never know.

21:12.344 --> 21:14.068
- I taught 'em young, Carl.

21:14.137 --> 21:16.931
Only reason to ride a bull,
meet a nurse.

21:17.000 --> 21:18.931
- Wouldn't be surprised
if nurses were behind

21:19.000 --> 21:20.206
the whole goddamned thing.

21:20.275 --> 21:23.068
Lord knows it ain't the pay.

21:23.137 --> 21:25.241
- Yeah.

21:25.310 --> 21:28.413
You know exactly what it is.

21:28.482 --> 21:30.482
- Shoot, I've told him
a thousand times

21:30.551 --> 21:31.827
I'd just give him
the damn buckle.

21:31.896 --> 21:33.275
- Well, that's the difference

21:33.344 --> 21:35.793
between raising a son
and a daughter.

21:35.862 --> 21:37.413
All you do with a daughter

21:37.482 --> 21:39.448
is just try to keep her
from getting screwed.

21:39.517 --> 21:43.379
All you do with a son is try to
keep him from screwing himself.

21:43.448 --> 21:47.517
- [laughs]
And that's a lot harder to do.

21:47.586 --> 21:51.724
- Well, that's why I'm here,
Carl.

21:51.793 --> 21:55.551
I need your help
to unscrew something.

21:55.620 --> 21:58.379
Your oldest boy said he saw
someone bring me to my house.

21:58.448 --> 22:00.034
- Yeah, that's what he told me.

22:00.103 --> 22:03.758
- Yeah, well, he's gotta
stop telling people that.

22:03.827 --> 22:07.172
- That's not what happened?
- That's exactly what happened.

22:07.241 --> 22:09.655
It's gonna cost me another son
if he keeps telling it.

22:09.724 --> 22:12.068
[Blur's "Song 2" playing]

22:12.137 --> 22:14.275
- Well, you tell me what
he should've seen doing,

22:14.344 --> 22:16.862
and by tomorrow
that'll be all he ever saw.

22:16.931 --> 22:19.793
You got my word.

22:19.862 --> 22:24.000
- ♪ Whee-hoo ♪

22:24.068 --> 22:25.551
- Thank you.

22:25.620 --> 22:27.620
- Derek de la Casa.
Here we go.

22:27.689 --> 22:29.965
[bull groans]

22:30.034 --> 22:32.103
[cheers and applause]

22:32.172 --> 22:33.931
All right, the move's
coming down eventually.

22:34.000 --> 22:35.586
- Oh.

22:35.655 --> 22:37.758
- Derek comes down
just a little bit early.

22:37.827 --> 22:39.586
- I hope I never meet the first
man who thought

22:39.655 --> 22:41.724
it was a good
idea to ride a bull.

22:41.793 --> 22:44.827
[chuckles]

22:46.965 --> 22:48.896
- I don't know, Carl.

22:48.965 --> 22:51.896
First man might be
worth meeting.

22:51.965 --> 22:53.517
It's the second man
I wonder about.

22:53.586 --> 22:55.206
- [laughs]

22:55.275 --> 22:57.034
- I believed the old marine
could do it.

22:57.103 --> 22:59.034
Let's give another big, big
round of applause

22:59.103 --> 23:01.517
for our hopeful Dan Tana.
Give it up again.

23:01.586 --> 23:02.620
Thank you.

23:07.137 --> 23:09.034
- Hmm.
[wolf howls]

23:09.103 --> 23:12.172
That's a big fucker
right there.

23:12.241 --> 23:15.448
Look at that.
That's a big fucking wolf.

23:15.517 --> 23:18.310
- I've done some morbid shit
on a first date,

23:18.379 --> 23:20.862
but this takes the cake, Rip.

23:20.931 --> 23:24.689
- It's far from a first date,
Beth.

23:24.758 --> 23:27.172
- Statute of limitations
on our first date

23:27.241 --> 23:28.724
ran out years ago.
- Oh, yeah?

23:28.793 --> 23:30.310
[chuckles]

23:30.379 --> 23:33.379
- When something dies
in the city, it's...

23:33.448 --> 23:36.241
It's roped off, zipped into
a bag and carried away

23:36.310 --> 23:38.551
before anyone can
bother to notice.

23:38.620 --> 23:40.551
- Mm.

23:40.620 --> 23:42.413
Well,
pretending it don't happen

23:42.482 --> 23:44.413
don't make it not happen.

23:44.482 --> 23:46.379
- That's very astute, Rip.

23:46.448 --> 23:47.827
I should embroider that
on a pillow.

23:47.896 --> 23:49.068
- [chuckles]

23:49.137 --> 23:50.344
- It makes you think
it doesn't.

23:50.413 --> 23:51.862
It's almost the same thing.

23:51.931 --> 23:53.655
- Oh, yeah, well,

23:53.724 --> 23:56.862
I hate to be the bearer of bad
news, but everything you know,

23:56.931 --> 24:01.000
and everyone you see everywhere
is gonna die.

24:02.965 --> 24:05.931
- You got old.

24:06.000 --> 24:10.000
- Mm, yeah.

24:12.103 --> 24:15.793
- God, you haven't aged a day.

24:17.000 --> 24:18.172
[chuckles]

24:18.241 --> 24:22.241
Shit, you might just
cheat death yet.

24:26.206 --> 24:28.241
Beth.

24:28.310 --> 24:32.931
- [screaming]

24:35.965 --> 24:37.689
- Beth.

24:37.758 --> 24:39.793
- [screams]
- Get!

24:39.862 --> 24:42.034
- [screams]

24:42.103 --> 24:43.413
- Get, get.

24:43.482 --> 24:47.137
both: [panting]

24:48.310 --> 24:50.827
- [breathing heavily]

24:50.896 --> 24:54.758
- You should try Zumba.
Get that cardio up.

24:54.827 --> 24:58.586
- What the fuck
is wrong with you?

24:58.655 --> 25:01.344
- Cheatin' death,
like you said.

25:01.413 --> 25:03.206
- [chuckles]

25:03.275 --> 25:05.551
You're the craziest person
I've ever met in my life,

25:05.620 --> 25:08.068
you know that?

25:08.137 --> 25:11.206
- It's only the things I love
that die, Rip, never me.

25:11.275 --> 25:14.000
[panting]

25:14.068 --> 25:15.517
Come to think of it,
I'm surprised

25:15.586 --> 25:19.206
you're still standing.

25:20.724 --> 25:23.344
Guess God ain't done
punishing you either.

25:23.413 --> 25:27.241
[wolf howls]

25:27.310 --> 25:29.448
[wolves howling]

25:29.517 --> 25:33.034
- [sighs]

25:33.103 --> 25:34.827
["Bad News" playing]

25:34.896 --> 25:37.620
[gunshots]

25:37.689 --> 25:39.448
- That's a triple.

25:39.517 --> 25:45.551
♪ ♪

25:45.620 --> 25:48.241
- ♪ Bad news travels
like wildfire ♪

25:48.310 --> 25:50.689
♪ Good news travels slow ♪
- Next up.

25:50.758 --> 25:52.896
- ♪ They all
call me Wildfire ♪

25:52.965 --> 25:55.793
- That's you, shit stain.

25:55.862 --> 25:57.931
- I'm gonna wait
for the water to warm.

25:58.000 --> 26:01.620
- You keep saying that
and keep not doing it.

26:01.689 --> 26:03.517
I'm the one who's gotta
sleep next to you.

26:03.586 --> 26:04.965
Take a fucking shower.

26:05.034 --> 26:07.724
- Cold shower's in your future,
Jimmy.

26:07.793 --> 26:09.241
Till they hire someone new.

26:09.310 --> 26:11.620
- So you might as well
get used to it.

26:11.689 --> 26:14.586
Shit. We did.

26:14.655 --> 26:16.310
- It's better than being dirty.

26:16.379 --> 26:20.517
- Gonna give it an hour.
- You'll be asleep in an hour.

26:20.586 --> 26:23.206
You smell like
a goddamned goat.

26:23.275 --> 26:25.586
Get up.
Get up.

26:25.655 --> 26:29.034
- ♪ Everywhere I go ♪

26:29.103 --> 26:30.517
♪ Oh ♪

26:30.586 --> 26:32.275
- Hey, man.

26:32.344 --> 26:33.862
- Looks like you're taking
that shower now, Jimmy.

26:33.931 --> 26:35.275
- I'm going.
Get the fuck off me.

26:35.344 --> 26:37.275
- Then fucking go.
- Get off, get the--

26:37.344 --> 26:40.103
[exhales deeply]

26:40.172 --> 26:42.655
♪ ♪

26:42.724 --> 26:46.413
- You can take my shower
in the morning, Jimmy.

26:46.482 --> 26:49.758
It's plenty hot then.

26:49.827 --> 26:53.758
Besides...

26:53.827 --> 26:55.551
♪ ♪

26:55.620 --> 26:59.724
a little cold water
don't bother me none.

26:59.793 --> 27:06.896
♪ ♪

27:09.482 --> 27:11.275
- ♪ Well, from north to south
and east to west ♪

27:11.344 --> 27:12.896
- Fuck you.

27:12.965 --> 27:15.344
- ♪ The story's all the same ♪

27:15.413 --> 27:18.344
[solemn music]

27:18.413 --> 27:25.413
♪ ♪

27:35.551 --> 27:37.241
- Where've you been,
sweetheart?

27:37.310 --> 27:39.379
- The park.

27:39.448 --> 27:42.655
What're you doing?

27:42.724 --> 27:45.034
- Trying to make a...

27:45.103 --> 27:49.068
Another decision a father
shouldn't have to make.

27:52.068 --> 27:56.034
What're your thoughts on...
judgment day?

27:56.103 --> 28:00.310
- It's every day
in my experience.

28:00.379 --> 28:05.068
- And the Bible says
a cremated body can't rise.

28:05.137 --> 28:07.241
- Well, fortunately,
that's not a decision

28:07.310 --> 28:09.310
you have to make today.

28:09.379 --> 28:13.448
- Yes, it is.

28:13.517 --> 28:15.862
- Something Lee did?

28:15.931 --> 28:19.965
- Something he didn't do.

28:20.034 --> 28:22.517
- Okay, who did?

28:22.586 --> 28:25.517
[ominous music]

28:25.586 --> 28:27.655
♪ ♪

28:27.724 --> 28:30.206
Then the decision's easy.

28:30.275 --> 28:32.034
Kayce was her favorite.

28:32.103 --> 28:35.758
And we promised to protect him.

28:35.827 --> 28:39.379
- Well, I've done
a piss-poor job of that.

28:39.448 --> 28:42.758
♪ ♪

28:42.827 --> 28:46.758
- You haven't broken it yet.

28:46.827 --> 28:53.862
♪ ♪

28:55.689 --> 28:58.724
[church bells ringing]

29:06.241 --> 29:09.241
- [grunts]

29:14.586 --> 29:18.068
- I remember
when you were a boy,

29:18.137 --> 29:20.413
up on scaffolding,

29:20.482 --> 29:24.137
hanging beams, right up there.

29:24.206 --> 29:26.034
[chuckles]

29:26.103 --> 29:30.931
I think that was the last time
you were in here.

29:32.000 --> 29:34.068
- Yeah.

29:34.137 --> 29:37.689
I've seen too much bad in
my life to believe God exists.

29:37.758 --> 29:39.068
[sniffles]

29:39.137 --> 29:41.275
- Guess you're here
just in case.

29:41.344 --> 29:43.724
- Yeah.
[chuckles]

29:43.793 --> 29:46.931
- Don't question the house
you've built, John.

29:48.689 --> 29:51.241
It's not uncommon

29:51.310 --> 29:54.241
to doubt one's faith
in the face of tragedy.

29:54.310 --> 29:57.068
It's when you need it most.

29:57.137 --> 30:01.827
Faith is where you
find comfort.

30:01.896 --> 30:04.275
- Well, I'm well past
seeking comfort.

30:04.344 --> 30:07.413
Uh, I'm here
for something else.

30:07.482 --> 30:11.172
- Any sins you've committed are
forgiven, John, you know that.

30:11.241 --> 30:15.275
All you have to do
is believe it.

30:15.344 --> 30:18.586
- Tell you the truth...
[chuckles]

30:18.655 --> 30:20.620
I don't regret one sin
I've committed.

30:20.689 --> 30:22.620
- [sighs]

30:22.689 --> 30:26.620
- It's the one I'm about
to commit that worries me.

30:26.689 --> 30:28.379
It should worry you too,
Father,

30:28.448 --> 30:31.034
because you're gonna
help me commit it.

30:31.103 --> 30:34.931
I'm collecting old debts, Bob.

30:35.000 --> 30:38.310
And you owe me a big one.

30:44.172 --> 30:47.172
- False witness.

30:47.241 --> 30:50.827
It seems odd that God would
find it necessary

30:50.896 --> 30:55.310
two Commandments that
instruct us not to lie.

30:56.482 --> 30:59.517
But the Ninth Commandment has
nothing to do with lying.

30:59.586 --> 31:03.586
It is about your neighbor.

31:03.655 --> 31:07.965
The men and women sitting
here with you today.

31:09.413 --> 31:12.482
It's about your flock.

31:12.551 --> 31:16.517
It is about your shepherds.

31:16.586 --> 31:19.482
And one of our shepherds

31:19.551 --> 31:22.034
is suffering.

31:22.103 --> 31:24.724
The pain of his loss

31:24.793 --> 31:28.551
reverberates throughout
this congregation.

31:28.620 --> 31:32.896
And his suffering is not over.

31:32.965 --> 31:35.482
Because Satan has
found

31:35.551 --> 31:38.344
an open window.

31:38.413 --> 31:42.379
And he is climbing through.

31:42.448 --> 31:46.551
The Ninth Commandment forbids

31:46.620 --> 31:49.206
speaking against your neighbor
in any manner.

31:49.275 --> 31:53.551
It forbids you from
destroying his reputation

31:53.620 --> 31:57.172
or threatening his position
or the sanctity of his family.

31:57.241 --> 31:59.793
Because his family
is your family.

31:59.862 --> 32:04.620
His flock is your flock.

32:04.689 --> 32:09.413
But Satan does not
attack the flock.

32:09.482 --> 32:13.172
He attacks the shepherd.

32:13.241 --> 32:15.620
He attacks him

32:15.689 --> 32:18.965
by tricking your mind.

32:19.034 --> 32:22.310
By making you see
what he wants you to see.

32:22.379 --> 32:26.241
And when he has
destroyed the shepherd,

32:28.137 --> 32:32.137
we are a flock no more.

32:34.000 --> 32:36.896
We are merely lambs

32:36.965 --> 32:40.344
awaiting the slaughter.

32:48.793 --> 32:51.758
Hello, Aaron.

32:51.827 --> 32:54.655
- Sometimes it, uh,

32:54.724 --> 32:57.448
feels like your sermons
are meant just for me.

32:57.517 --> 33:00.103
- Sometimes they are.

33:00.172 --> 33:02.758
I don't choose the sermon
or who it speaks to.

33:02.827 --> 33:06.379
My job is just to deliver it.

33:06.448 --> 33:08.310
[foreboding music]

33:08.379 --> 33:11.793
- I'm, uh...

33:11.862 --> 33:13.931
I'm having a...
- Let's...

33:14.000 --> 33:15.931
Let's go inside.

33:16.000 --> 33:18.206
♪ ♪

33:23.758 --> 33:25.931
- Hey, Cap, how's the team?

33:26.000 --> 33:27.379
- A little light right now.

33:27.448 --> 33:29.310
We leave for Riyadh in a week.

33:29.379 --> 33:31.827
Don't believe the hype on CNN,
brother.

33:31.896 --> 33:34.655
Syria ain't shit.
Yemen is the domino.

33:34.724 --> 33:38.379
Sure wish we had you here.
This shit's gonna get salty.

33:38.448 --> 33:40.965
- That's why I'm calling.

33:41.034 --> 33:42.620
I was thinking
about jumping back in.

33:42.689 --> 33:44.931
- Don't fucking tease me,
Kayce.

33:45.000 --> 33:47.206
- I wouldn't do it to you, sir.

33:47.275 --> 33:49.517
You can get me
back on the team?

33:49.586 --> 33:52.275
- You're not a year
from discharge, are you?

33:52.344 --> 33:55.172
- Uh, just under.

33:55.241 --> 33:58.310
- Then hell yes, I can.
Pack your shit, sailor.

33:58.379 --> 34:00.068
- I never unpacked it.

34:00.137 --> 34:03.275
- Stay by your phone.
Keep your powder dry.

34:03.344 --> 34:06.000
And get ready to fly.

34:06.068 --> 34:09.275
- Roger that.

34:14.068 --> 34:17.447
- We're gonna be late.

34:17.516 --> 34:20.447
[ominous music]

34:20.516 --> 34:22.241
♪ ♪

34:22.310 --> 34:26.724
What did I do?

34:26.793 --> 34:28.757
- You didn't do anything.

34:28.827 --> 34:33.379
- Okay, what did you do?

34:33.447 --> 34:36.413
- It's what I can't do.

34:36.482 --> 34:39.551
I can't provide for
a family selling horses.

34:39.620 --> 34:41.344
- Maybe you could if you'd
actually sell 'em

34:41.413 --> 34:44.447
and not give them away.

34:44.516 --> 34:48.068
- I got two skills,
and only one of them pays.

34:48.137 --> 34:49.793
I'm not gonna have my wife
providing for my family--

34:49.862 --> 34:53.034
- Don't you dare invent a way
to make this my fault.

34:53.103 --> 34:55.724
You had no problem being a
broke horse trainer a week ago,

34:55.793 --> 34:57.896
and neither did I.

34:57.965 --> 34:59.758
What, you let your father
back in and all of a sudden

34:59.827 --> 35:01.620
going to war is
the best option?

35:01.689 --> 35:04.172
- I'm no good at this, Monica.

35:04.241 --> 35:06.103
- Ain't that the truth.

35:06.172 --> 35:09.482
You might be the worst liar
I've ever met.

35:09.551 --> 35:13.068
So just stop lying and tell me
why you're leaving us.

35:14.344 --> 35:16.620
- I just--
- The truth, Kayce.

35:16.689 --> 35:20.517
We've always told it.
Don't stop now.

35:20.586 --> 35:21.862
- I was the one--

35:21.931 --> 35:26.068
[explosion]

35:26.137 --> 35:27.310
[tires screech]

35:27.379 --> 35:30.931
[engine revs]

35:31.000 --> 35:33.448
You all right?
- Yeah.

35:33.517 --> 35:36.000
What was that?
- Meth lab's my guess.

35:36.068 --> 35:39.275
Call 911.
Stay here.

35:50.551 --> 35:51.758
[tense music]

35:51.827 --> 35:53.724
[dog whimpers]

35:53.793 --> 36:00.896
♪ ♪

36:14.517 --> 36:16.931
- Family.

36:17.000 --> 36:19.517
♪ ♪

36:19.586 --> 36:23.413
Family.
Family.

36:23.482 --> 36:24.931
♪ ♪

36:25.000 --> 36:27.517
Family.

36:27.586 --> 36:30.551
- You ain't got one no more.

36:30.620 --> 36:33.068
- Kill me.

36:33.137 --> 36:36.206
Kill me.

36:36.275 --> 36:38.206
Kill me.

36:38.275 --> 36:42.965
♪ ♪

36:43.034 --> 36:45.655
- Hey, I've got 911.
Are there people back there?

36:45.724 --> 36:49.827
- Not anymore.

36:49.896 --> 36:51.551
- What're you doing?

36:51.620 --> 36:54.517
- Stay here.
- No.

36:54.586 --> 36:57.172
♪ ♪

36:57.241 --> 36:58.586
- You don't wanna see this.

36:58.655 --> 37:01.793
- Kayce, I go where you go.

37:01.862 --> 37:04.758
- Okay, fine.
Cover your mouth.

37:04.827 --> 37:07.758
Don't breathe in the fumes.

37:07.827 --> 37:14.862
♪ ♪

37:20.034 --> 37:22.551
- Please kill me.

37:22.620 --> 37:25.655
- How long on the ambulance?

37:25.724 --> 37:27.103
How long on the ambulance?

37:27.172 --> 37:29.000
- The--they said 45 minutes.

37:29.068 --> 37:33.862
- Kill me.
- He ain't got 45 minutes.

37:33.931 --> 37:37.137
There's no pain like burning.

37:37.206 --> 37:40.965
♪ ♪

37:41.034 --> 37:43.448
- Do it.

37:43.517 --> 37:50.517
♪ ♪

37:55.034 --> 37:57.448
[chatter on radio]

37:57.517 --> 38:01.034
- Oh, it was
the right thing to do.

38:01.103 --> 38:04.551
- No question.

38:04.620 --> 38:08.724
- What do you wanna do?

38:11.689 --> 38:14.206
- I'm not ready
to play this hand.

38:14.275 --> 38:17.413
Not like this.

38:17.482 --> 38:21.482
Just make it go away.

38:23.413 --> 38:25.620
You got off easy.

38:25.689 --> 38:28.620
I would've let you burn.

38:28.689 --> 38:31.068
- I hear you SEALs
like the G-19.

38:31.137 --> 38:34.137
That what you used?

38:36.896 --> 38:39.379
Give me your slide.

38:39.448 --> 38:42.448
I like 'em too.

38:42.517 --> 38:45.551
[gun clicks]

38:47.241 --> 38:48.620
You were there.

38:48.689 --> 38:51.206
I put that piece of shit
out of his misery.

38:51.275 --> 38:52.862
Understand?

38:52.931 --> 38:55.206
You're my witness.

38:55.275 --> 38:57.862
I'll put it that way
in my report.

38:57.931 --> 39:00.137
- Okay.

39:00.206 --> 39:02.241
- Follow my vehicle
with your truck.

39:02.310 --> 39:04.551
- Uh, we gotta pick
our kid up from school.

39:06.689 --> 39:11.000
- We are covered in evil.
You and me.

39:11.068 --> 39:14.206
We gotta wash it off.

39:14.275 --> 39:17.206
[foreboding music]

39:17.275 --> 39:24.275
♪ ♪

39:25.172 --> 39:28.586
You know what I think?

39:28.655 --> 39:32.655
I think a man who does that
to himself never changes sides.

39:34.103 --> 39:37.137
I know I won't.

39:37.206 --> 39:40.931
- I didn't do this to myself.

39:41.000 --> 39:43.758
We don't get
to choose our fathers.

39:43.827 --> 39:46.241
- Wouldn't make any difference
if we could.

39:46.310 --> 39:49.931
We'd just choose wrong.

39:50.000 --> 39:54.137
Son doesn't look like you.

39:54.206 --> 39:56.344
- No.

39:56.413 --> 39:58.896
He got lucky.

39:58.965 --> 40:02.448
- Looked like you when
he was born, though, didn't he?

40:02.517 --> 40:05.379
Just like you.

40:05.448 --> 40:08.620
- Like a mirror.

40:08.689 --> 40:12.068
- Every child looks like their
father when they're born.

40:12.137 --> 40:14.827
Doesn't matter, boy or girl.

40:14.896 --> 40:17.896
Doesn't matter who they look
like three days later.

40:17.965 --> 40:19.827
When they come out of the womb,

40:19.896 --> 40:24.000
they are a perfect reflection
of the man who made them.

40:24.068 --> 40:26.448
- He was.
[sniffles]

40:26.517 --> 40:29.931
- You wanna know why?

40:30.000 --> 40:33.758
It's nature's way of proving
that you are the father.

40:33.827 --> 40:37.896
So that you don't think the
baby belongs to someone else,

40:37.965 --> 40:41.482
and kill it.

40:41.551 --> 40:45.068
There's no such thing
as a good man, Kayce.

40:45.137 --> 40:48.482
All men are bad.

40:48.551 --> 40:53.068
But some of us try
real hard to be good.

40:53.137 --> 40:55.551
- Stones are ready.

40:55.620 --> 40:59.413
- Your first sweat?

40:59.482 --> 41:02.965
The ceremony doesn't end
when the sweat ends.

41:03.034 --> 41:06.172
Study the things you see.

41:06.241 --> 41:09.344
They're a map of your future.

41:09.413 --> 41:11.793
The good thing about maps

41:11.862 --> 41:14.862
is if you don't like
the path that you're on,

41:14.931 --> 41:18.448
you can always choose another.

41:18.517 --> 41:22.448
♪ ♪

41:22.517 --> 41:24.965
- When does the ceremony end?

41:25.034 --> 41:28.793
- When you die,
and the next one begins.

41:28.862 --> 41:35.896
♪ ♪

41:44.310 --> 41:47.241
[ominous music]

41:47.310 --> 41:54.310
♪ ♪

42:00.241 --> 42:07.310
♪ ♪

42:12.448 --> 42:15.206
[body bag zips]

42:15.275 --> 42:17.551
♪ ♪

42:17.620 --> 42:20.689
[chainsaw whirring]

42:20.758 --> 42:27.793
♪ ♪

42:47.620 --> 42:53.689
♪ ♪

42:53.758 --> 42:56.689
[cart rattling]

42:56.758 --> 43:03.068
♪ ♪

43:03.137 --> 43:05.931
- This oven will incinerate
a horse in an hour.

43:06.000 --> 43:08.965
Never had a person in it,
though.

43:09.034 --> 43:13.482
My guess is you'll have ashes
in about ten minutes.

43:13.551 --> 43:17.896
[incinerator whooshes]

43:17.965 --> 43:25.000
♪ ♪

43:35.206 --> 43:42.206
♪ ♪

43:49.724 --> 43:56.758
♪ ♪

43:59.241 --> 44:01.965
[engine revving]

44:06.275 --> 44:13.103
♪ ♪

44:20.965 --> 44:23.896
[horn honking]

44:23.965 --> 44:27.172
♪ ♪

44:27.241 --> 44:30.172
[splattering]

44:30.241 --> 44:37.241
♪ ♪

44:45.724 --> 44:52.758
♪ ♪

45:09.517 --> 45:14.241
- Why do you do that?
[tool clinks on floor]

45:14.310 --> 45:18.310
Make you feel better?

45:19.862 --> 45:23.137
- Makes it so
I don't feel anything.

45:23.206 --> 45:25.862
- Mm.

45:25.931 --> 45:29.689
Well, what're you
trying to forget?

45:29.758 --> 45:33.344
- Everything.

45:33.413 --> 45:37.206
- If you were willing to forget
everything, I wouldn't be here.

45:39.827 --> 45:41.758
- Fine.
You wanna go?

45:41.827 --> 45:43.137
Do you wanna fucking go?
[drill whirs]

45:43.206 --> 45:45.931
You wanna?
[clanks drill on metal]

45:46.000 --> 45:48.482
Huh?
- Come on.

45:48.551 --> 45:51.862
- [grunts]

45:55.758 --> 45:57.448
- Hey, sweetie.

45:57.517 --> 46:00.275
You want a bug book
or a snake book?

46:00.344 --> 46:03.413
- Dinosaur book.

46:06.310 --> 46:08.586
- You want me
to read it to you?

46:08.655 --> 46:11.827
- No. My dad needs to
because we found one.

46:11.896 --> 46:13.517
And it's out secret.

46:13.586 --> 46:16.034
You can't know about it,
'cause if you tell someone,

46:16.103 --> 46:17.655
they might steal it.

46:17.724 --> 46:19.137
- Well, Daddy's not here,
honey,

46:19.206 --> 46:20.655
so you're either gonna
have to tell me the secret

46:20.724 --> 46:23.896
or settle for
looking at pictures.

46:23.965 --> 46:27.586
- Pictures.
- Suit yourself, kid.

46:32.310 --> 46:34.241
- What's the green one do?

46:34.310 --> 46:35.655
- It's oxygen.

46:35.724 --> 46:39.551
- Mm-hmm.
Go on, pull that one too.

46:39.620 --> 46:40.758
[oxygen hisses out]

46:40.827 --> 46:42.103
That's enough.
Come here.

46:42.172 --> 46:43.965
I want you to take
these tools here

46:44.034 --> 46:45.655
and put 'em in the tray.

46:45.724 --> 46:47.724
- I don't want to.
- That ain't what I asked you.

46:47.793 --> 46:49.655
- Come on, man,
can we talk about this?

46:49.724 --> 46:51.689
- You had your chance.
- I-I will never say a word.

46:51.758 --> 46:54.551
I swear to God.

46:54.620 --> 46:57.206
Please.
- Why are you so scared?

46:57.275 --> 46:59.206
- I don't wanna die.

46:59.275 --> 47:00.724
- No?

47:00.793 --> 47:03.827
Don't seem like
you wanna live either.

47:03.896 --> 47:05.413
So which one is it?
Wha--ah--ah.

47:05.482 --> 47:06.931
Which one is it?

47:07.000 --> 47:10.000
- [whimpers]

47:12.241 --> 47:14.620
- You see,
it's the habit of living

47:14.689 --> 47:18.517
that you're scared of losing.
That's all.

47:18.586 --> 47:22.862
Now, pick the fucking tools up

47:22.931 --> 47:25.206
and put 'em in the tray
like I asked you.

47:25.275 --> 47:28.275
- Yeah.
[sighs]

47:32.344 --> 47:34.965
That's enough.
Now come over here.

47:35.034 --> 47:37.965
Now we're gonna put it
in the microwave.

47:39.896 --> 47:42.172
Now, don't move.

47:45.965 --> 47:49.275
Is this the only computer
that's got this report?

47:49.344 --> 47:52.517
- Yeah.

47:52.586 --> 47:54.724
- Not the one at your house?

47:54.793 --> 47:57.448
- No. Wha--who do you think
this is gonna fool, man?

47:57.517 --> 47:59.068
Everyone's gonna know
this is arson.

47:59.137 --> 48:02.620
- No, no, it don't look
like arson to me.

48:02.689 --> 48:05.620
Looks like suicide.

48:05.689 --> 48:07.000
- Uh-huh.

48:07.068 --> 48:11.241
- Deep down that's
what you want, isn't it?

48:11.310 --> 48:13.551
Yeah.

48:17.758 --> 48:20.379
- Can I have one?

48:20.448 --> 48:24.448
- Sure, go ahead.

48:36.206 --> 48:37.689
- [gasps, coughs]

48:37.758 --> 48:40.655
[grunts]

48:40.724 --> 48:43.655
[menacing music]

48:43.724 --> 48:50.758
♪ ♪

48:58.448 --> 49:01.551
[microwave buttons beeping]

49:01.620 --> 49:08.655
♪ ♪

49:15.068 --> 49:20.862
♪ ♪

49:20.931 --> 49:23.965
- [sighs]

49:43.620 --> 49:46.655
- If I'm gonna lose you,
it's gonna be

49:46.724 --> 49:49.379
because of what I did,
not because I lied to you.

49:52.413 --> 49:55.310
- If I give you this lie,
will you stay?

49:57.068 --> 49:58.586
- Well, if I stay,
you'll learn it.

49:58.655 --> 50:00.965
- Well, I guess that's
what we meant

50:01.034 --> 50:04.551
when we said for
better or for worse.

50:04.620 --> 50:07.758
- It's gonna get
worse than this.

50:07.827 --> 50:11.068
- Daddy.

50:11.137 --> 50:14.275
- Please say you'll stay.

50:14.344 --> 50:17.448
- Whatever I do, it's because
I love you, I'll say that.

50:19.482 --> 50:22.586
- Baby, look at me.

50:22.655 --> 50:26.034
There is nothing you could do
I won't forgive you for.

50:27.689 --> 50:29.862
- Yeah, there is.

50:33.827 --> 50:35.689
- Daddy.

50:35.758 --> 50:40.068
- I wanna be with my son.

50:40.137 --> 50:43.413
♪ ♪

50:43.482 --> 50:46.724
- Do you think ours
is as big as that one?

50:46.793 --> 50:50.758
- I don't know.
Might be bigger.

50:50.827 --> 50:54.793
- We need to dig him up
tomorrow.

50:54.862 --> 50:58.448
- Well, we can start, but
that's gonna be a lot of work.

50:58.517 --> 51:01.586
- I ain't scared of work.

51:01.655 --> 51:05.517
Where should we hide him?

51:05.586 --> 51:07.655
- Mm, at the barn.

51:07.724 --> 51:09.724
- No, people will look there.

51:09.793 --> 51:12.344
[gasps] Maybe we
should dig a cave.

51:12.413 --> 51:14.793
- [chuckles]

51:14.862 --> 51:17.793
Whatever you want, buddy.

51:17.862 --> 51:20.827
[acoustic country music]

51:20.896 --> 51:24.724
- ♪ Spending time today ♪

51:24.793 --> 51:27.275
♪ Is the only way ♪

51:27.344 --> 51:31.379
♪ To buy a new tomorrow ♪

51:31.448 --> 51:32.758
♪ ♪

51:32.827 --> 51:35.413
♪ And I'll agree ♪

51:35.482 --> 51:37.724
♪ That you and me ♪

51:37.793 --> 51:42.034
♪ Have the same price to pay ♪

51:42.103 --> 51:43.413
♪ ♪

51:43.482 --> 51:45.724
♪ For nothing sane ♪

51:45.793 --> 51:47.482
♪ Was ever gained ♪

51:47.551 --> 51:50.034
- You know,

51:50.103 --> 51:53.172
most fathers don't have to...

51:53.241 --> 51:56.000
Don't have to do this twice.

51:56.068 --> 51:59.482
Since I do, I thought I'd bring
you some company, sweetheart.

51:59.551 --> 52:03.827
- ♪ Forever seldom lasts ♪

52:03.896 --> 52:06.965
♪ Good-bye, yesterday ♪

52:07.034 --> 52:09.517
♪ Good-bye, dreams ♪

52:09.586 --> 52:13.586
♪ I won't be dreaming ♪

52:13.655 --> 52:16.655
♪ Good-bye, memories ♪

52:16.724 --> 52:20.551
♪ Of a love
I thought was true ♪

52:20.620 --> 52:21.827
♪ ♪

52:21.896 --> 52:24.896
♪ Good-bye, reasons why ♪

52:24.965 --> 52:27.172
♪ I cried all night ♪

52:27.241 --> 52:31.827
♪ And wished
that I could die ♪

52:31.896 --> 52:36.000
♪ Good-bye, yesterday ♪

52:36.068 --> 52:38.241
♪ Yesterday ♪

52:38.310 --> 52:41.896
♪ Good-bye ♪

52:41.965 --> 52:45.034
♪ At the break of day ♪

52:45.103 --> 52:48.896
♪ I'll find a way ♪

52:48.965 --> 52:53.000
♪ To face the new tomorrow ♪

52:53.068 --> 52:54.379
♪ ♪

52:54.448 --> 52:57.000
♪ And with the dawn ♪

52:57.068 --> 52:59.482
♪ I'll carry on ♪

52:59.551 --> 53:03.586
♪ And I'll have no regrets ♪

53:03.655 --> 53:05.310
♪ ♪

53:05.379 --> 53:07.965
♪ Oh, memories ♪

53:08.034 --> 53:10.758
♪ Of you and me ♪

53:10.827 --> 53:14.241
♪ Will fade and pass away ♪
